audio_descriptions.notes:
7:92 - Stick is tied to a string and hanging from a branch. Crow flies off another branch.

22:56 - Food is pushed back into long box, out of reach.

55:39 - Crow lands on table where experiment is being recorded

59: 35 - Crow searched table

1:01:59 - Crow spots food inside see through box

1:04:45 - Crow checks other box with bars on front side

1:07:52 - Crow checks box with food again, figuring out how to get it

1:12:75 - Crow spots stick hanging from string

1:16:11 - Crow flies onto branch where string is tied with stick hanging down

1:21:55 - Crow tried to figure out how to get the stick 

1:26:72 - Crow bites string and pulls it up, using his feet to hold it down. He is shortening the string

1:37:83 - Crow begins untying stick from string, using its beak and feet 

1:43:37 - Crow successfully gets the stick untied from the string, then proceeds to fly off the branch and back onto the table

1:47:80  - Crow inspects box with bars on front side

1:50:27 - Crow hops over to see through box with food inside

1:52:81 - Crow attempts to pull food out of box, but realizes stick is too short

1:55:26 - Crow hops back over to box with bars on front side

1:58:40 - Crow pulls longer stick out of that box with the short stick

2:02:94 - Crow drop short stick and picks up longer stick 

2:06:65 - Crow moves back over to box with food inside

2:09:06 - Crow uses the longer stick to pull the food out of the box

2:16:64 - Crow successfully pulls food out of box, and proceeds to eat it
